reviews.text:
We ordered a 14" Chicago Stuffed Crust pizza (The Monster) and a 12" Deep Dish pan pizza (Chipotle BBQ chicken) for 9 people. They were both amazing and delicious! The cheese pull is fantastic and they were VERY generous with their ingredients. Very affordable as well - It was worth way more than what we paid.

The stuffed crust was perfectly crisp on the outside and the tomato sauce complemented all the toppings that were inside the pizza. The Chipotle BBQ chicken had a mildly sweet and tangy BBQ sauce that shined through the chicken and other toppings. 10/10 would come back!

I also saw that they also sell single slices of pizza which would be perfect if you're just craving pizza or for a date night.

We also loved the staff! They are the nicest people you can ever meet. Thank you for being so kind and patient with us! And for accommodating our large group with such short notice.
Great food and service. Caesar salad was tasty. Fire roasted chicken tortellini was really good. Food came out fast. Highly recommend coming here to eat.

I tried this place looking for a place that would hopefully become a new "regular" pizza place.  I would describe the food as average and/or plain.

The prices are OK for what you get, and they have a good selection, but just expect a very average meal.  I would describe the pizza as comparable to a very good frozen pizza.

The final nail in the coffin for me was when I ordered desert.  I ordered a slice of turtle cheesecake, and the waitress brought me a fully frozen piece and even admitted they didn't have any thawed pieces.  That alone would have been OK, but the cheesecake tasted like a cardboard box.  Not the best I've had, to say the least.

Oh, and there were a bunch of fruit flies that wouldn't leave me alone at the table.

I didn't even realize there was a restaurant here because it doesn't look like there us from outside. But inside is surprisingly spacious. We came during Happy Hour so I tried the Midnight Spaghetti which was the marinara and Alfredo sauces combined. It was good, basically a creamy pasta sauce. We also ordered a 10" pizza which was a good price for the price and customization. I will probably be back next time I get a tire rotation nearby.

This is neighborhood tavern in a strip mall, so there is ample parking.  Service was excellent, and likewise the pizza.  We went with an extra large (16") Monster, substituting jalapenos for mushrooms.  The house made crust was a little thicker than the usual thin crusts, which is a positive because the slices remained firm throughout the meal.  No mushy pizza here.  At $23.99, we would consider this a bargain.

We also ordered onion rings, fries, and a Chicago dog.  The latter was a bit disappointing, the casing on the wiener being so tough that I needed a knife to cut through it.  Eating a Chicago dog with a knife and fork took away from the experience.

Add in a couple of beers and a soft drink, and the meal before tip came to $63.16.  Lots of leftover pizza made this a good buy.

editorial_summary.overview: Sizable dining room featuring a menu of Chicago-style pizzas & hot dogs, burgers & pasta entrees.

We recently placed an online takeout pizza order.  The online ordering was easy to use.  When we arrived at the restaurant at the scheduled pick-up time, we only had to wait about a minute for the pizza to come out of the oven.  We had ordered a stuffed pizza, and it was fantastic.  Everything from the ingredients to the baking was perfect.
The atmosphere in the restaurant seemed nice.
I would've shared a picture of the pizza, but it disappeared before I could take a photo of it.
We will definitely be ordering from this Frankie's again.

detailedReviews.author: Niki
detailedReviews.text: Spaghetti and chicken Alfredo was BLAND! There is nothing authentic about this place and places specifically in Minnesota needs to stop advertising their restaurants like this! It was my 1st and last time. I noticed the deep dishes slices in the window was NOT even close to an Chicago deep dish, cheese looks like GMO, doesn't looks like it melts properly, sauce looks extremely BLAND as well! And the folks that were dining in looked like they didn't know what SEASONED food nor what authentic Chicago foods is either. Only thing I noticed was that the salads lettuce looks really crisp, so I guess that's a good thing. I wouldn't recommend this place at all unless you're just near by and want a beer.

detailedReviews.author: Douglas Ferrie
detailedReviews.text: The wife and I had a night off while the kids were at their grandparents. So we decided to give Frankie‚Äôs a shot. We have lived in the area for 10+ years and my wife loves deep dish. So we decided to give er a try. We arrived and the place was packed. Nothing wrong there. We waited at the hostess stand for a solid 5 min before anyone even acknowledged we were there. It‚Äôs busy, we can let it slip. We got sat down and started to look at the menu. Waitress came over got our drinks and then we asked if we could have a min to look over the menu. 15 min later and multiple times of our waitress walking passed us without a single check in. My wife tried to get her attention a few times, with no luck. We finally ordered (buffalo wings, Cesar salad, 4 meat pizza). Wings were quick to get out. They were fine, pretty average at best 6/10. The salad was underwhelming and equivalent to a cheap bag salad. The pizza arrived and I took the first bite. Instant disappointment. Sauce was under seasoned and lack luster. luckily the thick, bland and very generic pizza dough was there for filler. The topping tasted frozen and and bland‚Ä¶see the on going trend? My wife and I didn‚Äôt make it through a single slice on our own. We left 3/4 a pizza on the table when we left. Do not eat here. They don‚Äôt deserve your money and your taste buds can do way better at any of the other local pizza options. Not sure how they can keep their doors open with his level of garbage service and food. 2/10 overall rating.

detailedReviews.author: Ben Matlock
detailedReviews.text: One of the better pizzas in town. Has been twice named the best by Minnesota Monthly. The ambiance of the place is warm and cozy. The main room is nice , and they have a party room in back that's all very comfy. The staff is very friendly and accommodating. The food , non- pizza has improved vastly. Their ribs, burgers and chicken have all gotten better. Prices are reasonable. They come up a bit short on dessert , and I'm a big dessert person or else I'd be giving them 5 stars. One thing to be noted is so many people on the staff have worked there for 5 to 12 years which speaks to it being a first class restaurant .

detailedReviews.text: Out-of-towners trying for the first time. Just a standard pepperoni and sausage and they absolutely killed it. The sauce was surprisingly good. The inside of the place was super clean and lots of people enjoying their food. Will definitely try again when passing through.

detailedReviews.author: Mike Nelson
detailedReviews.text: Delicious!

detailedReviews.author: Ras Kafka
detailedReviews.text: Great family place that doesn't feel so family oriented that someone like myself can't sit down and get my grub on with a couple of beers. It never has out of control kids running around or screaming which is a huge plus! Food is all top rate, authentic, real deal Chicago style. Grab a piece of plain cheesecake for dessert if you still have room for it. Well curated beer list on tap and in bottles. Not massive selection, but guaranteed to satisfy beer snobs and all regular beer drinkers. Staff is incredibly nice and welcoming. They even have open mic nights where I got to see genuine local talent trying out original songs alongside some rather arcane covers. One of my new favorite places since moving to the NW metro.
